name: Notes: Nested frames with auto layout are used to wrap groups of components (AppBar, Navigation and Body each have their own frame with auto layout enabled, for example) This also allows for each of these primary sections to have their own grid based on material standards (12-column with gutters & margin is shown here) Stack elements can be used to manage vertical or horizontal groups of elements that can be inserted into instance slots (Cards for To Do and State Application, for example) MUI components are used with only built-in options used for customization There are a number of places where creating a custom composite component will be needed to achieve full fidelity to designs, for example: Logo and text in App Bar Progress text and last confirmed/attested text on Progress Cards Count next to To Do and Communications Card titles Scrollable list on To Do and Communications Cards Custom stack of Text, Buttons and Icons on Communication Cards In addition to extending components to achieve the design there are some components that need further clarification and decision on what to use from MUI Kit :)
characters:
Notes:

Nested frames with auto layout are used to wrap groups of components (AppBar, Navigation and Body each have their own frame with auto layout enabled, for example)
This also allows for each of these primary sections to have their own grid based on material standards (12-column with gutters & margin is shown here)
Stack elements can be used to manage vertical or horizontal groups of elements that can be inserted into instance slots (Cards for To Do and State Application, for example)
MUI components are used with only built-in options used for customization
There are a number of places where creating a custom composite component will be needed to achieve full fidelity to designs, for example:
Logo and text in App Bar
Progress text and last confirmed/attested text on Progress Cards
Count next to To Do and Communications Card titles 
Scrollable list on To Do and Communications Cards
Custom stack of Text, Buttons and Icons on Communication Cards
In addition to extending components to achieve the design there are some components that need further clarification and decision on what to use from MUI Kit :)
